#: ../../T/terminak.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Caltech, ca. 1979] Any malfunctioning computer terminal. A common failure "
"mode of Lear-Siegler ADM 3a terminals caused the ‘L’ key to produce the ‘K’ "
"code instead; complaints about this tended to look like \"Terminak #3 has a "
"bad keyboard. Pkease fix.\" Compare :ref:`dread-high-bit-disease`\\, "
":ref:`frogging`\\; see also :ref:`sun-stools`\\, :ref:`HP-SUX`\\, "
":ref:`Slowlaris`\\."
msgstr ""
"[Caltech、1979年ごろ]あらゆる故障中のコンピュータ端末。Lear-Siegler ADM "
"3a端末によくある故障モードでは、‘L’キーが‘L’コードの代わりに‘K’コードを生成した。これについての苦情は\"Terminak #3 has a "
"bad keyboard. Pkease fix.\"のように見える傾向があった。\\ :ref:`dread-high-bit-disease`\\ "
"、\\ :ref:`frogging`\\ と比較せよ。\\ :ref:`sun-stools`\\ 、\\ :ref:`HP-SUX`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`Slowlaris`\\ も参照。"
